The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, December 21, 2003  Business Briefs																								 Chennai, Dec. 20: Chennai-based SSI and Scandent group are planning to merge their information technology services. The proposed new entity, in which SSI and Scandent will hold equal equity, will be a mid-sized IT services company with a projected combined annual revenues of $60 million and 1100 employees. The arrangement involves demerger of SSIs software service business as a listed entity and merging into Scandents IT services business.																								 New Delhi, Dec. 20: BSNL today said there are no roaming charges for BSNLs mobile services  CellOne and Excel. The customer has to pay only nominal charges as applicable in home network for making local, STD or ISD calls and there is no additional charge of any sort, BSNL said here. 																								 Mumbai, Dec. 20: Gold moved in a narrow range and closed steady, while silver recovered smartly on the bullion market here today. Standard gold (99.5 purity) opened steady at Rs 6,105 and eased marginally to end at Rs 6,100. Ready silver (.999 fineness) opened firm at Rs 9,150 and ended at the same level, a recovery of Rs 45 over yesterdays close of Rs 9105.
